.TH hsh 1 "18/08/2022" "hsh(1)" "hsh - General Commands Manual"

.SH NAME
.B Simple_Shell - hsh - emulate to the basics sh shell.
- a custom command language interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DECRIPTION
The hsh simple shell is a command languages interpreter taht executes commands read from a command line string, the standar input, or a specified file, this shell tries to be a mini copy of the unix shell created by Ken Thompson.

.SH OVERVIEW
Read, interpret and execute the commands sent to the terminal.

.SH INVOCATION
Compile simple_shell with the GNU Commpiler Collection, using gcc plus the below specified flags:
.B $ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh

Interactive Mode
.B ($) ./hsh
Non Interactive Mode
.B echo "ls" | ./hsh

.B USAGE
command -flags
.B Example
"ls -al"

.SH BUILTINS
The following builtin commands are supported:
.B exit - exit to shell
.B env - prints the environment variables

EXAMPLE USAGE

($) ls
README.md   built_in.c   functions_str.c   main.h   'Shell flowchart.jpg'   functions_aux.c   hsh.c   _printf.c   functions_help.c

echo "pwd" | ./hsh
/home/manurodriguez/holberton/holbertonschool-simple_shell

